cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper focuses on mapping the supply of new knowledge from public research organizations, which involves analyzing scientific production indexed in the Web of Science. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and citation analysis (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an algorithm for the reconciliation of authors' affiliations, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software development (cs.SD).
